task.summary: Default task

AnnotationToolApplication (javafx version of AnnotationTool) coupled to the FXControllerBox, although most of the features have not been implemented yet. Currently just makes circles based on the color picked.
toggleClickable works slightly better. DOes not bring to front until mouse is released.
javaannotatefx implements undo.
redo implemented. Error with undo trying to undo on empty stack fixed.
Text feature added to javafx version of AnnotationTool. In this version, there is no bug where you can't undo single characters made in sequence. Toggle Clickable feature also added.
added ability to "Enter" for a new line when creating text.
clear history button now works in FX.
Now cannot draw while toggle clickable is false.
Saving images now works on windows.
Small whitespace additions.
Fixed some bugs with handling the zoom events.
Commenting change.
Ability to add circles of any size added.
Added some notes to comments from the meeting.

Changes the way that things are drawn. Now we have one stage whose opacity is set to 0.004 that registers all the mouse events. There is another stage who renders all these events as drawings. This should fix the issue with catching mouse events in the linux version.
As it currently works, the stage that renders the drawings does not yet follow the stage that picks up the listeners. The one that picks up the listeners can be moved around with the title bar (Although the bar is hard to see). This does lead to some bugs if you try and move the stage currently.
Another change that was added was a cosmetic change to the ControllerBox. Now, the color picker is centered.
Should fix linux bug where stage is not maximized.

The stage that is drawn on will now follow the movement and size of the stage that registers all of the mouse events. Still need to change the toggle clickable option so that it will work with the new layout of two stages.
Some notes were added at the bottom as comments.
Increased opacity of builder so that user can visualize the area that they are creating. Some small changes have been begun to detect what os is being used and react accordingly.
Fixed issue where button resize popup required you to press okay twice.
Tool tips when hovering over buttons in the controllerbox now are larger.
Zoom commented out
Border has been added. Follows any resizing done to stages. Changed code for moving so does not currently work to move for 2 fingers, just works to resize for now.
Added option to move stage around with option on controllerbox.
You can now move the stage with two fingers, as well as resize the stage with two fingers (touch events)
Fixed bug where you would start drawing while moving the window if you used one touch to move the window and then tried to move it again (while in moving mode).
Removed unneeded TODOs and added in a few as well.
Fixed null pointer exception when you click the draw option before adding any text.

Fixed bug where the iconcontrollerbox did not follow the stage properly if you start maximized/fullscreen.
Stage technically never starts maximized or full screen now. Will simply fit to the screen (basically still full screen).
removed some unneeded TODOs.
Fixed issue where iconcontrollerbox would not relocate when the window changed size.
Fixed issue where changing button sizes would lead to the picture stage going over top of the mouse catchingstage.
Moving shape feature mostly finished. Still need to iron out bugs with redo/undo on shapes that are moved after being erased.
Moving shape feature now works even if you erase, then move, then undo, then redo, then redo.

Now, if you move text, it will give you the option to edit the text on it similar to if it were just added. When undone, it undoes changes, giving you whatever was originally typed, and when redone, it redoes changes.
merge successful
push new branch
Support is begun for saving changes to a file through the classes in the saveItems package.
